reviewText: Well alot of people say this might be a waste if you hav seen them in concert already. I don't care. I have seen them once live in the 6 or 7 years i have been into them so a live concert is always a treat. Good performances by both ICP and ABK. Good trailer for the new backyard wrestling game as well. You get songs from all 6 jokers cards and other albums of course. some songs in case you are not aware of are:Tilt a whirl,dead body man,Let's go all the way,murder rap,chicken huntin,birthday b*ches,F' the world,and many others. over 30 songs in all including the abk set. so get this,even if you aren't a juggalo you'll get into this.

reviewText: I bought this DVD after I bought Hell's Pit that came with the free concert DVD. The concert that came with Hell's Pit is awesome, but this is a lot better. The stage set is bigger and more detailed than the one of the Hell's Pit DVD. This concert is also longer and has a few songs done by ABK. This is worth buying even if you have the concert that came with the Hell's Pit record. Here's the songs they do on this DVD. I'll put a * next to the ICP songs that are on here that aren't on the concert you get with Hell's Pit. The songs that are on here are:Welcome To The ShowDead Body ManTilt-a-WhirlBlaaam!!!Birthday B#tchesAssassinsChicken Huntin* Willy BubbaLet's Go All The Way* Your Rebel Flag* Cemetary GirlF#ck The WorldDown With The Clown* The Old School Sh#t* Stomp* I Want My Sh#tMurder RapHomies* Hall of Illusions* Hell's Forcast* Everybody Rize* Dog Beats* Thy Staleness* Pass Me By* Juggalo Anthemand the songs that ABK does areYa Neden's HauntedGhetto NeighborCome Out To PlayHated MeToolsHollowpointFoodangHood RatsGang Related

reviewText: The introduction to this DVD is sweet. "Anybody Killa" or A.B.K. does the introduction and it's great. He does classic songs like "Ghetto Neighbor" and "Gang Related." Insane Clowns come in about 20 minutes into the video and they tear it up. The sound quality is much better than the Wicked Wonka Tour Video that comes with Hell's Pit Version 2. There are a lot of songs. The review below shows all the songs they play. The one thing that bugged me through Insane Clown Posse's performance is that the echo on Jay and Shaggy's mics was up too loud for most of the time. It's an easy thing to ignore but that's really the only down to the DVD. 2 thumbs up, 10/10, great DVD! mmfcl

reviewText: After buying three ICP Joker's Cards (Wraith: Shangri-La, Amazing Jeckel Brothers and Great Milenko), I figured out I should buy this DVD, because I would finally watch the guys in a show (unfortunately, they'll probably never play here in Brazil, so I guess I'll never see them live).Enough talk, let's get to the facts... The show itself is awesome, includes songs from their beggining until songs from their last album until the moment: The Wraith - Shangri-La. Their performance is great, and totally hilarious. If I was only judging this DVD for the show itself, it would obviosly get the whole five stars, but that's not all I judge.The DVD sound is Stereo, but I wished it was 5.1, it would sound much, much better. The image is a little bad, they could've... mastered it somehow, couldn't they? What about the extras? Everything we have in here is a trailer from Backyard Wrestling: Don't Try This At Home videogame (avaliable for PlayStation 2 and Xbox). I'm not saying this trailer sucks. In fact, this trailer rocks so much, Backyard Wrestling will be my next game for the Xbox. I can't wait to wrestle people as Violent J or Shaggy 2 Dope. But couldn't they put some videoclips (Juggalo Homies videoclip would be a sweet extra) or backstage footage as extras? It wouldn't hurt anyone, and I'm sure every juggalo would love this DVD even more if it had more extras. Am I not right?Even though is lacks of extras, doesn't have that amazing sound or image quality, this DVD rocks and it's a must buy for any Juggalo living anywhere in this universe. Juggalo love, y'all!
